result.name: Ah Yat Harbour View Restaurant

reviews.text: Had dimsum lunch at Ah Yat HarborView.  Enjoying the view of the harbour and overall quite good dimsum.  Supposedly Michelin Star but no standout dish for me.  However, saw that a couple of tables ordered the braised oxtail in claypot which smelled so good.  Alas, just too much food to order that as well so have to skip.
Attentive service, and top quality chinese cuisine

We came to have lunch for the quietness and space for conversation. We were able to stay from 1.00 pm to 4:00 pm and left when the cleaner came around to hoover the floor.

Don’t order the Char Shui Bun though, not only it is small in size, it lacks the firmness that a good bun normally has.
Foods are quite exceptional and so are the prices. Service are excellent.
Great food with nice harbour view

reviews.text: Isquare  Is a nice shopping mall it has really call art work in front of it. It's really busy has a lot of nice shops that are all open past 10:00 p.m. It's in a convenient location from the Subway. Has some good restaurants in it. And the movie theater

It's a modern and great design shopping center and close to my hotel. I went here for a lunch and found Mark & Spencer on the ground floor and shopped a bit here. Overall, it's a nice shopping center.
Good for shopping (M&S clothing and food hall, marketplace), kids-r-us and other kid brands, very good cinema, linked to TST MTR train station
Visited the EyeLounge.  Very nice location with breath taking views of the city! Good drinks and very nice restaurant and cuisine.
High end shopping mall in Kowloon. Big brands.
